[bq="Number1pegasus"]Also more cute animal stories. Back at my old school we had an animal lab where you'd get to look at the animals they had there.

They had a Rabbit there. And they let us hold him.

Literally, every kid that got to hold him the Rabbit would be jumping around and want to leave.

I get to hold the Rabbit. Nothing. Absolutely nothing. All he did was laz around in my arms and do nothing.

All the other kids were like "....H-How?" [/bq]
It could be the manner in how you hold the bunny.
If you don't hold it right, the bunny will fill uncomfortable and will jump.
But is kinda weird cuz rabbits doesn't like to be high up for long time, he was probably tired to move after all the jumps.
